  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Thursday. I woke up feeling ill, with a fever so high I could feel it in my own eyebrows, if that is even medically possible.",
      "zh": "星期四。我一早醒來就覺得很不舒服，發燒燒到我連自己的眉毛都能感覺到熱，如果這在醫學上真的可能的話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My throat hurt, my whole body ached, and I was so thirsty I drank an entire cup of water in about four seconds.",
      "zh": "我喉嚨痛，全身痠痛，還渴到一杯水大概四秒鐘就喝光了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom took one look at me and announced, with the confidence of a doctor, \"That is the flu. Straight back to bed.\"",
      "zh": "媽媽看了我一眼，就用醫生般的自信宣布：「這是流感，馬上回床上去。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad brought medicine and a thermometer, and Sophia brought a bowl of hot soup that she insisted would cure almost anything.",
      "zh": "爸爸拿來藥和溫度計，Sophia 則端來一碗熱湯，她堅持這碗湯幾乎什麼病都能治。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"There is no real cure for a common cold or the flu,\" Dad said gently. \"You just have to rest until your body fights it off.\"",
      "zh": "「一般感冒或流感其實沒有真正的特效藥，」爸爸溫柔地說：「你只能休息，讓身體自己把它打敗。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia looked personally offended by that comment and insisted her soup had cured worse things than a simple fever.",
      "zh": "Sophia 一臉像被冒犯了一樣，堅持她這碗湯治好過比一個小小發燒還嚴重的病。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My stomach felt strange too, somewhere between a stomachache and just general disease-related misery.",
      "zh": "我的胃也怪怪的，介於胃痛跟一般生病帶來的難受感之間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, being a very sensitive and caring brother, stood at my doorway and asked if the flu was contagious through video games.",
      "zh": "William 這位非常貼心又體貼的哥哥，站在我房門口，問流感會不會透過電動傳染。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I told him medically speaking, no, but emotionally speaking, I was too tired to explain the difference to an eight-year-old.",
      "zh": "我跟他說，就醫學來說不會，但就情緒層面來說，我實在太累了，沒力氣跟一個八歲小孩解釋這中間的差別。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By Friday, my fever had gone down and I felt strong enough to recover slowly on the couch, wrapped in three blankets.",
      "zh": "到了星期五，我的燒退了，感覺自己有力氣可以慢慢在沙發上恢復，裹著三條毯子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I still could not go to school, so Bernice video-called me and updated me on every tiny piece of school news I had missed.",
      "zh": "我還是不能去上學，所以 Bernice 打視訊電話給我，把我錯過的每一件學校小事都更新給我聽。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"You picked a bad week to be sick,\" she said. \"Today was the annual health checkup, and it was chaos.\"",
      "zh": "「你挑了一個生病的壞時機，」她說：「今天是年度健康檢查，超級混亂。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "According to Bernice, the school nurse checked everyone's weight, measured their ankle reflex with a tiny rubber hammer, and looked into their ears and eyes.",
      "zh": "根據 Bernice 的說法，校護量了每個人的體重，用一支小小的橡皮槌測了大家的腳踝反射，還檢查了大家的耳朵和眼睛。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One boy apparently jumped so hard when his ankle was tested that he nearly fell off the chair, which Bernice found extremely funny.",
      "zh": "有個男生腳踝被測反射的時候彈跳得太用力，差點從椅子上摔下去，Bernice 覺得這超級好笑。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The nurse also checked their tongues, skin, and nails for anything unusual, and gently asked if anyone was having any pain anywhere.",
      "zh": "校護也檢查了大家的舌頭、皮膚跟指甲有沒有異常，還輕聲問大家有沒有哪裡覺得疼痛。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One kid mentioned a painful toothache, and the nurse recommended he see a dentist as soon as possible.",
      "zh": "有個孩子提到牙齒很痛，校護建議他儘快去看牙醫。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The class also watched a short health video about the human body, mentioning how organs like the liver quietly clean the blood every single day.",
      "zh": "班上還看了一段關於人體的短片，提到肝臟這類器官每天都默默地在清理血液。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The video briefly mentioned diseases like cancer, explaining that scientists around the world are still working hard to find better treatments and cures.",
      "zh": "影片也簡短提到癌症之類的疾病，說明全世界的科學家仍在努力尋找更好的治療方法和藥物。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice admitted the video made her a little nervous, but also weirdly grateful that her own body works pretty well most days.",
      "zh": "Bernice 坦白說這段影片讓她有點緊張，但也讓她意外地感激自己的身體大部分時候都運作得還不錯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time we hung up, I felt lucky my flu was just a flu, and not anything more serious than a few days on the couch.",
      "zh": "掛掉電話的時候，我覺得自己很幸運，我的流感就只是流感，沒有比在沙發上躺幾天更嚴重的問題。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: nothing makes you appreciate a healthy body like spending three days unable to trust your own stomach.",
      "zh": "今日心得：沒有什麼比連續三天連自己的胃都不能信任，更能讓人懂得珍惜健康的身體了。"
    }
  ],
